Car manufactures design vehicle systems that are adequate for the average driver. If you drive your car harder than average you will over tax the systems, especially the brakes. Precise application of braking is essential for competitive lap times, even in short events like auto cross and track-day competitions.
For 43 years Baer Brakes has participated in every type of racing and performance activity. Thru Racing, Baer Brakes first recognized the need for improvements in brakes for street performance vehicles. Baer is the brand most recognized among serious performance vehicle owners because they work better and deliver the best performance value.
Below is a brief overview of Baer's brake systems:
SS4+ (Front) - Designed for 15" wheels (perfect for RestoMods and restorations where modern brakes are a must. This system features our S4 (4 piston caliper) on an 11" 2-pc rotor.
SS4 (Rear) - Designed for 16" (and some 15" wheels) this is the same looking caliper as the SS4+ front but mounted to a 12" 1-pc rotor with a drum in hat park brake.
SS4+ (Rear) - Designed for 17" or larger wheels, this is a perfect match to the Pro+ or Ext+ front (as a more affordable rear package). The SS4+ features a 13" 2-pc rotor and drum in hat park brake.
Track4 (Front)- Designed for 17" or larger wheels. The Track4 features our larger T4 caliper mounted to a 13" 1-pc rotor. The Track4 works great with the S4 rear.
Pro+ (Front or Rear) - Designed for 17" or larger wheels (available in front or rear, and in 13" or 14" rotors). This is the first offering that we have that you can get the EXACT same look front and rear.
Extreme (Front or Rear) - This is our largest brake offering and features a 2618 Forged monoblock caliper mounted to a 14" 1-pc rotor. The Extreme is available in front or rear (for that EXACT same look), but only for a few select applications. Most of our Extreme offerings are Extreme+ (2-pc rotors).
Extreme+ (Front or Rear) - This is our largest brake offering and features a 2618 Forged monoblock caliper mounted to a 14" 2-pc rotor. The Extreme+ is available in front or rear, for the EXACT same look.



SS4+ 11" Front




Available in 18-gauge polished stainless steel or traditional steel with powder coat finish
Grille guard is shaped to match the lines and contours of your specific vehicle
1.5" diameter tubing provides high level of rigidity and strength
Vertical bumper sections are padded with protective black polyurethane
Headlight guard slats are removable
Pre-drilled holes allow easy mounting of auxiliary lights and equipment



SS4+ 11" rear (NO park brake)




Looks exactly like the SS4+ 11" front
All the benefits of our larger brake systems just in a smaller package to fit 15" wheels
Perfect system for someone looking to retain factory 15" wheels, or the enthusiast the that wants to have a larger wheel with the option to go back to the stock look
Everything needed per corner (including hoses and fittings) except for in General fit applications
Features a 1" directionally vaned slot, drill, zinc plated rotor



SS4 12" rear (with drum in hat park brake)




Features a 1-pc 12" directionally vaned slot, drill, 
Perfect match for our Track4 front brake
Fully machined billet backing plate that also holds the drum in hat park brake
Features a "Banksia" park brake. More modern design of a common drum in hat. Uses the same shoe as a late model corvette
Complete with all hoses, fittings and hardware
12" rotors will fit some 15" and most 16" wheels.
Verify fitment with a template.
Standard colors are Red, Black or Silvers.



